basics.name: Albert Einstein
basics.label: Scientist
basics.summary: A Mechanical Engineering graduate with a passion for custom fabriation and design, especially in cinema.

work.name: Texas A&M University Engineering Capstone
work.summary: Worked with a team of 5 other Senior Mechanical Engineering Students to research, design, and fabricate a Pistol Recoil Simulator over the course of 2 semesters.
highlights: Development of Realistic Design Requirments with Client

work.name: Eaton Aerospace
work.summary: Was contracted into the position I created during my previous internship to automate Excel spreadsheets. During this time I created dashboards that visualzed worker productivity data across the manufacturing floor.

work.name: Eaton Aerospace
work.summary: Took the initiative to teach myself Visual Basic for Application to automate the data entry tasks given to me as an intern. Eventually, I created an Excel program to automate the incident report process for the manufacturing facility.

work.name: Fischer Engineering Design Center Machine Shop, Texas A&M University
work.summary: Oversaw shop floor to ensure safe operation of shop tools and machinery as well as answer any fabrication questions from shop users. Also completed fabrication requests machining parts to specific dimensions within specified tolerances.

work.name: North Asheville Little League Baseball
work.summary: Teaching at Palmer Physical Laboratory (now 302 Frist Campus Center). While not a professor at Princeton, I associated with the physics professors and continued to give lectures on campus.
